    <item>
      <title>Episode 38: .NET MAUI, IoT, and Handy the bionic Arm - with Clifford Agius</title>
      <link>https://unhandledexceptionpodcast.com/posts/0038-cliffordagius/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 08 Jun 2022 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://unhandledexceptionpodcast.com/posts/0038-cliffordagius/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;In this episode, I was joined by &lt;a href=&#34;https://twitter.com/CliffordAgius&#34;&gt;Clifford Agius&lt;/a&gt; to chat about both .NET MAUI, and also developing for IoT. (These were separate topics - not specifically IoT on MAUI). Clifford is an airline pilot who&amp;rsquo;s also a freelance .NET developer who regularly blogs and speaks at conferences around the world!&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;MAUI (Multi-platform App UI) is a new .NET framework for building multi-platform apps - both mobile (iOS/Android) and desktop (macOS/Windows) using C# and XAML in a single codebase. It also supports Blazor components for those that prefer that over XAML.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
